The paper deals with scene text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of self-attention mechanism and deep learning models also suggests that it could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses benchmarking and empirical analyses, which could indicate information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category.
